# Dev → prod workflow (FrontBill)

## During development — do NOT

- Run new SQL scripts on **production** Supabase while still coding or testing.
- Point local `.env.local` at production Supabase keys for daily work.
- Merge to `main` without testing on **dev/staging** Supabase first.

## Before merging to main — remind the user to confirm

- [ ] Tested on **dev/staging** Supabase
- [ ] PR reviewed
- [ ] New SQL listed in PR with **“run on prod after deploy”**

## After merge to main — remind the user to confirm

- [ ] Vercel **production** deploy succeeded
- [ ] Run **new SQL scripts in prod Supabase only** (never before deploy unless intentional)
- [ ] Quick smoke test on live URL

## Environment split

- **Local** (`pnpm dev`): `.env.local` → staging Supabase + `SUPABASE_ENV=staging`
- **Vercel Production**: prod Supabase keys only
- **Vercel Preview / Development**: staging Supabase keys
- **SQL scripts in repo**: updating Git does not change any database until run manually in Supabase SQL Editor per project

When the user discusses merges, PRs, SQL migrations, Vercel deploys, or prod releases, surface this checklist proactively.
